summary: Valkyrie, A Standalone Follower I assembled thanks to the user guides. Please Note this is my first ever mod and unfortunately I was not able to add everything I would have liked (see screens). Please give all credit to all those listed authors (and anyone who I may have forgotten) as they are the true creators of all that you see.
descriptionHtml:
[font=Tahoma][b]

[center][size=6]Valkyrie
[size=5][i]The Battlemage[/i][/size][/size][/center]

[/b][center][size=5][b]Stats:[/b][/size]
[size=4]Nord
Spell Sword
Essential
Marriageable
Voice: Female Sultry (because everyone is fricking young eager!0
Body Type: UNP


[b][size=5]Location:[/size][/b]
You will find her in the Riften Jail.

[b]
[size=5]Attributes:[/size][/b]
I think she may be an overpowered battle mage/tank.
She has perks for both Light & heavy Armour, lots of destruction spells (including frost
cloak), some healing spells and one handed perks.
Also she has a higher Magicka[b] [/b]count.
[/size]
[font=Tahoma][size=4][b]
[youtube]OQaFPasTIk4[/youtube]

See Time: 05:03

https://youtu.be/OQaFPasTIk4?t=303[/b][/size][/font][/center]
 [size=4][b]
Future Plans[/b][/size]:
[/font]Depending on the interest,  I plan to make some further updates to appearance, spells & customized Armour/Weapon. More importantly though, I hope to create a story arc involving her, new world spaces, other NPC's and another potential follower. Without giving too much away, In the quest you learn why she is in Jail & agree to help her. in her quest which brings her to skyrim & to seek you out. [font=Tahoma][size=5]
[/size]
[b][size=4]Known bugs:
[/size][/b]-KS hairdo's renewal may be a dependency (thank you tessmess1), I will check this and make any updates if necessary. For now if you experience a problem re this, I would highly recommend you install the hair pack anyway.  Seriously it is awesome

-Valkyrie is sometimes outside her jail cell (unintended), I think that is because of her
factions  (or rather current lack of until I get the quests going) and AI package (like Serana's). I cannot change that for now & it’s hardly game
breaking, so please don’t ask. It is neither a problem, just an issue with her location until I get the quests going in future updates.
 [size=4]
[b]Re Compatibility/conflicts/bugs: [/b][/size]
I will say this, I have been a mod user for some time & I cannot foresee this causing any major problems with any mainstream
follower mods, however I cannot guarantee this, nor can I say that there are no
dirty edits. If anyone does notice anything then I apologize in advance but all
I will say is you were warned ;P
 
At the end of the day, my knowledge of modding is really basic at the moment. Therefore I may be able to help with
some issues, but anything else more complicated and my answer will be:  
 [img]data:image/jpeg;base64,[/img]
 

Fortunately there is a good community here and hopefully someone will be able to answer your question if you ask nicely :D


[b][size=4]Installation:
[/size]NMM recommended. Manually install by copying folders into the appropriate folder, i.e.
C:\Steam\steamapps\common\Skyrim\data\(appropriate folders). For those
who have never manually installed a mod, use NMM or any other popular
mod organizer.


[size=4]Credits[/size][/b]:

I have not really created anything original, merely assembled a follower based on other people’s assets, instructions and hard work.
Therefore please endorse & give all credit to the authors I have listed including anyone who I may have forgot to mention as they are way more
deserving.

[/font][font=Tahoma][size=4][b]Permissions:
[/b][size=2][font=Tahoma]You do not need my permission for any edits, videos personal usage etc. However Please do not upload anywhere else and respect the permissions of other authors and people who I have credited for asset use. [/font][/size][b]
[/b][/size][/font][font=Tahoma]
[size=4][b]Misc Info: [/b][/size]
I cannot stress enough that this is my first ever mod! So therefore please be patient with me & if I have forgotten someone
or something, let me know so that I can make any changes. It has never
been my intent to showcase anything I have done as my own work. It still amazes
me, how many talented people there are on this site, so please respect
everyone’s contribution & hard work.
I wanted to do a follower mod to learn how to use CK and hopefully learn to develop this mod and create further ones.
Therefore I present this follower. I think she is standalone however I am not
entirely sure. Also I was disappointed that I was not able to make all of the
original changes I had intended (i.e. scars & makeup, see screens) as I had
allot of trouble with tints etc. Hopefully someone can point out where I went
wrong. Please feel free to make any changes you wish but do not charge or re-upload
the mod.
A Big Thank you to the nexus community and especially Bad Apple Pie's video tutorial. Without this, I would have been
unable to complete this mod [url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3I1nvXOb3T4]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3I1nvXOb3T4[/url]
 
Any bugs or issues please don’t hesitate to let me know. I cannot guarantee I will or can do anything about them though. Use
at your own risk, I am not responsible for you breaking your game!
 
:D
[/font]
